.TH NF 1 "January 2026" "nf 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nf \- command-line nutrition facts tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nf
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
[\fIFOOD_ITEM\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nf
is a command-line tool that provides macronutrient information (protein, carbohydrates, and fat) for food items using the USDA FoodData Central API.
.PP
The tool queries the USDA nutrition database and displays nutritional information in a clean, color-coded format. When multiple food items are specified, it also displays total macronutrients.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-setup \fIAPI_KEY\fR
Configure the USDA FoodData Central API key. The key is stored in ~/.config/nf/config.json
.TP
.B \-\-help, \-h
Display help information and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Get nutrition facts for a single food:
.B nf apple
.TP
Get nutrition facts for multiple foods:
.B nf chicken breast rice broccoli
.TP
Foods with spaces require quotes:
.B nf "sweet potato" "peanut butter"
.TP
Configure API key:
.B nf \-\-setup YOUR_API_KEY_HERE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/nf/config.json
Configuration file containing the USDA API key
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (no API key configured, API error, or invalid usage)
.SH API KEY
To use this tool, you need a free API key from the USDA FoodData Central:
.PP
.RS
https://fdc.nal.usda.gov/api-key-signup.html
.RE
